<p>Colorado Springs residents can take advantage of multiple incentive layers for solar and HVAC improvements. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Colorado state incentives include property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes. The state also offers sales tax exemptions on solar equipment purchases, saving residents additional hundreds of dollars on system costs.</p>

<p>Springs Utilities participates in net metering programs, allowing solar customers to receive retail rate credits for excess electricity fed back into the grid. The utility also offers rebates for energy-efficient HVAC equipment, including up to \$400 for high-efficiency heat pumps and \$200-\$600 for efficient furnaces and air conditioners. Additional rebates are available for smart thermostats, duct sealing, and insulation improvements. These combined incentives can reduce the total cost of solar and HVAC upgrades by 35-50%, making energy improvements highly attractive investments for Colorado Springs homeowners.</p>

